1.Display customer_id, city  who lives either in ‘CLT’ or in ‘TVM’

mysql> select id,city from Customer where city="calicut" or city="trivandram";
+----+------------+
| id | city       |
+----+------------+
|  4 | calicut    |
|  5 | trivandram |
|  6 | calicut    |
|  7 | calicut    |
+----+------------+
4 rows in set (0.00 sec)

******************************************************************************************************

2.Display product details with an updated price amount(new price= old price+5rs)

mysql> select * from Product;
+-----+------------+-------+
| pid | pname      | price |
+-----+------------+-------+
| 101 | soap       |   122 |
| 102 | maggie     |    26 |
| 103 | jelly      |     3 |
| 104 | dinner set |  1020 |
| 105 | book       |   510 |
| 106 | tea        |   255 |
| 107 | dairymilk  |    61 |
| 108 | pen        |     5 |
+-----+------------+-------+
8 rows in set (0.00 sec)

mysql> update Product set price=price+5;
Query OK, 8 rows affected (0.00 sec)
Rows matched: 8  Changed: 8  Warnings: 0

mysql> select * from Product;
+-----+------------+-------+
| pid | pname      | price |
+-----+------------+-------+
| 101 | soap       |   127 |
| 102 | maggie     |    31 |
| 103 | jelly      |     8 |
| 104 | dinner set |  1025 |
| 105 | book       |   515 |
| 106 | tea        |   260 |
| 107 | dairymilk  |    66 |
| 108 | pen        |    10 |
+-----+------------+-------+
8 rows in set (0.00 sec)
